## 5. UI/UX Design System

### 5.1 Style and personality

The CALM Platform is a **professional enterprise tool** for architects and developers. The visual language is **minimal-functional** — clean, information-dense where needed, never cluttered. Reference: Linear, Vercel Dashboard, Retool.

- **Primary style:** Clean minimal with subtle depth. No glassmorphism, no skeuomorphism, no heavy gradients.
- **Dark mode:** Both light and dark themes. Dark is the default. Design and test both independently.
- **Iconography:** Lucide React only. No emoji as icons. No mixing icon styles.
- **Single primary CTA per page.** Secondary actions are visually subordinate.

### 5.2 Color system — semantic tokens only

No raw hex values in components. All colours defined as CSS custom properties and Tailwind config tokens.

```
/* Backgrounds */
--color-bg-primary        /* page background */
--color-bg-secondary      /* sidebar, cards, panels */
--color-bg-tertiary       /* hover states, subtle fills */

/* Borders */
--color-border            /* default card borders, dividers */
--color-border-strong     /* active/focused borders */

/* Text */
--color-text-primary      /* headings, labels */
--color-text-secondary    /* descriptions, metadata */
--color-text-tertiary     /* placeholders, hints, group headers */

/* Brand */
--color-brand             /* primary CTA, active nav, links */
--color-brand-hover
--color-brand-muted       /* backgrounds behind brand text/icons */

/* Status — always combined with a text label, never colour alone */
--color-status-draft      /* amber */
--color-status-review     /* blue */
--color-status-published  /* green */
--color-status-deprecated /* muted red */

/* Feedback */
--color-error             /* constraint violations, validation failures */
--color-warning           /* drift detected, soft warnings */
--color-success           /* validation passed, published */
--color-info              /* neutral informational */
```

**Light theme:** Background white/slate-50/slate-100. Text slate-900/slate-600/slate-400. Brand indigo-600. Border slate-200.

**Dark theme:** Background zinc-950/zinc-900/zinc-800. Text zinc-100/zinc-400/zinc-600. Brand indigo-400. Border zinc-800.

All foreground/background pairs must meet **WCAG AA 4.5:1** for normal text and **3:1** for large text and UI components. Verify both themes independently.

### 5.3 Typography

| Role | Size | Weight | Line-height |
|---|---|---|---|
| Page title | 24px | 600 | 1.3 |
| Section heading | 18px | 500 | 1.4 |
| Card heading | 14px | 500 | 1.4 |
| Body text | 14px | 400 | 1.6 |
| Caption / meta | 12px | 400 | 1.5 |
| CALM JSON / code | 13px (JetBrains Mono) | 400 | 1.7 |
| Canvas node label | 12px | 500 | 1.3 |
| Badge / tag | 11px | 500 | 1 |

- Font family: Inter for all UI text; JetBrains Mono for all code and CALM JSON.
- Type scale: 11 / 12 / 13 / 14 / 16 / 18 / 20 / 24 / 32.
- Minimum visible text: **11px**. Never smaller.

### 5.4 Spacing — 4pt/8pt grid

All spacing values must be multiples of 4px.

```
4px   tight inline gaps (icon-to-text)
8px   between related elements
12px  compact component padding
16px  standard component padding, card padding
24px  section gaps
32px  major section separation
48px  page-level top padding
```

- Sidebar width: 220px (collapsible to icon bar at < 1024px)
- Content max-width: 1280px
- Content horizontal padding: 32px desktop, 16px tablet
- Breakpoints: 768px / 1024px / 1440px

### 5.5 Navigation (sidebar)

- Persistent on desktop (≥ 1024px). Collapses to icon bar on tablet (768–1024px).
- Items: 20px icon + label text. Never icon-only at full width.
- Active item: 2px left border in `--color-brand` + `--color-bg-tertiary` background + `--color-text-primary` label.
- Group headers: 10px, uppercase, `--color-text-tertiary`, letter-spacing 0.08em.
- Maximum 2 levels of hierarchy. No nested sub-menus.
- Breadcrumb on every page below depth 1. Format: `Section / Sub-section / Page`.

### 5.6 Buttons

- **Primary:** `--color-brand` background, white text. One per page.
- **Secondary:** `--color-bg-secondary` + `--color-border` + `--color-text-primary`. For secondary actions.
- **Destructive:** Danger/red. Spatially separated from primary. Confirm before all destructive actions.
- **Ghost:** No background/border. For tertiary icon actions.
- Minimum height: 36px (compact tables), 40px (standard forms).
- Loading state: spinner replaces label; pointer events disabled.
- Focus ring: 2px solid `--color-brand`, 2px offset. Never hidden.

### 5.7 Status badges

Always combine colour with a text label. Never colour alone.

- Draft: amber. In Review: blue. Approved: indigo. Published: green. Deprecated: muted red.
- Drift score: green (0), amber (1–5), red (> 5).
- Quality score: red → amber → green transitions at 40 and 70.

### 5.8 Cards

Background: `--color-bg-secondary`. Border: `--color-border` (1px). Radius: 8px. Padding: 16px.
Hover: `--color-border-strong` + subtle shadow lift. Do not shift layout on hover.
Shadow scale: `none` → `0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.12)` → `0 4px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.15)`.

### 5.9 Tables (TanStack Table)

- Header: `--color-bg-secondary`, uppercase 11px labels, `--color-text-tertiary`.
- Row height: 48px standard, 40px compact. Hover: `--color-bg-tertiary`.
- Sort icon shown on hover of sortable columns; active column shows directional arrow.
- Sticky header on scroll. `aria-sort` on all sortable columns.

### 5.10 Forms

- Visible label above every input. No placeholder-only labels.
- Input height: 40px standard. Error below the relevant field (not only at top). Required fields marked `*`.
- Helper text below complex inputs: 12px `--color-text-tertiary`.
- Validate on blur, not on every keystroke. Focus first invalid field after submit error.
- Disabled state: 0.5 opacity, `cursor: not-allowed`, semantic `disabled` attribute.

### 5.11 CALM Canvas (React Flow)

- Background: `--color-bg-primary` with subtle dot-grid pattern (`--color-border` dots, low opacity).
- Nodes: `--color-bg-secondary` fill, `--color-border` stroke (1.5px), 8px radius. Primary label `--color-text-primary`, type sub-label `--color-text-tertiary` 11px.
- Node type left-border accents (not fill colours): service = indigo, database = emerald, system = amber, network = cyan, human-actor = violet, generic = gray.
- Selected node: `--color-brand` stroke (2px) + subtle glow.
- Error node: `--color-error` stroke (2px) + error tooltip on hover.
- Edges: `--color-text-tertiary` stroke (1.5px). Animated dashes for unsaved-changes state.
- Minimap: bottom-right, 160 × 100px. Controls: top-right (zoom in/out, fit view).
- Node palette panel: left, 200px, grouped by CALM type category, draggable items.

### 5.12 Analytics (Recharts)

- Every chart: visible legend, axis labels with units, tooltips on hover, accessible colour palettes.
- Series colour order: indigo → emerald → amber → rose → cyan. Never red/green only pair.
- Empty state: explicit message + CTA. Never an empty axis frame.
- Loading state: skeleton shimmer. Never blank.
- All interactive chart elements must have keyboard focus support and `aria-label`.
- Date range picker on every chart: 7d / 30d / 90d / custom.

### 5.13 Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

- Contrast: body text ≥ 4.5:1, large text and UI components ≥ 3:1. Both themes.
- Focus rings: 2px solid `--color-brand`, 2px offset. Never removed without a custom ring.
- Keyboard navigation: all interactive elements reachable via Tab. Order matches visual order.
- Aria labels: all icon-only buttons have `aria-label`. All inputs have associated `<label>`.
- Status changes: `aria-live="polite"`. Errors: `role="alert"`.
- Reduced motion: all animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (instant or cross-fade fallback).
- Heading hierarchy: sequential h1 → h6, no skipped levels.
- Tables: `aria-sort` on sortable columns, `scope` on header cells.

### 5.14 Animation

- Duration: 150–250ms for micro-interactions, 300ms for page transitions. Never > 400ms.
- Easing: `ease-out` for entering, `ease-in` for exiting.
- Animate only `transform` and `opacity`. Never animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`.
- Page transitions: fade + 8px upward translate on enter; fade on exit.
- Canvas node add: scale from 0.85 + fade in (150ms).
- Toast: slide from bottom-right + fade. Auto-dismiss at 4 seconds.
- All animations interruptible. Never block user interaction during animation.

### 5.15 Governance review page layout

- Split: 60% canvas diff (left), 40% review panel (right).
- Pre-check checklist: ✓ green, ⚠ amber, ✗ red — with icon + text (never colour alone).
- Decision buttons: Approve (primary/green), Request Changes (secondary/amber), Reject (destructive/red). All require confirm dialog.
- Reviewer annotation pins on canvas: numbered circles in `--color-brand`.

